    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Proprietary name for an analog videocassette format developed by Sony in 1969, using 3/4" tape with a running speed of 3.75 inches per second. The format was popular in semi-professional industrial, educational and broadcast contexts from the 1970s until the advent of digital video technology.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
